Package: apsystems-stock
Version: v1.1.1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: OpenAPS <bdbruin@gmail.com>
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Depends:
Description: Wraps the stock APsystems firmware so it can be disabled and restored.
 Installed = stock active (the factory default). Removing this package DISABLES
 the stock firmware: it comments the manager launch in /etc/rcS.d/S50ecu_init
 (so no stock app starts at boot) and stops the running manager + its inverter
 and web supervisors (monitor.exe/main.exe, lighttpd, thttpd, mqtt.exe).
 Reinstalling restores the manager launch (reboot to relaunch stock).
 Disabling the manager also stops idwriter and macapp, so the prerm refuses
 unless reboot-persistent dropbear (openaps-dropbear / S98) and the S39 eth0
 MAC-setter are already installed.
